  "body": "### Component\n\nFoundryup\n\n### Have you ensured that all of these are up to date?\n\n- [X] Foundry\n- [X] Foundryup\n\n### What version of Foundry are you on?\n\nunknown\n\n### What command(s) is the bug in?\n\nfoundryup\n\n### Operating System\n\nLinux\n\n### Describe the bug\n\nWhen building a docker image with foundry in it the docker build fails with a permissions error on the `foundryup` line. But if I comment this out and then run `foundryup` inside the running container it installs fine. The dockerfile is running (at that point) as the `node` user which is the same user I'm running the command as manually.\r\n\r\nDockerfile:\r\n```docker\r\nFROM mcr.microsoft.com/vscode/devcontainers/typescript-node:0-14\r\n\r\n# Update all Ubuntu Packages\r\nRUN apt-get update && apt-get upgrade -y\r\n\r\n# Install all apt-get packages\r\nRUN apt-get install -y curl \\\r\n    python3-pip\r\n\r\n# Install node.js\r\n# RUN curl -fsSL https://deb.nodesource.com/setup_14.x | sudo -E bash -\r\n# RUN apt install -y nodejs\r\n\r\n## Install the Hardhat (hh) shortcut tool\r\nRUN npm install -g hardhat-shorthand\r\n\r\n#Install rust\r\nUSER node\r\n    RUN curl --proto '=https' --tlsv1.2 https://sh.rustup.rs -sSf | sh -s -- -y\r\nUSER root\r\n\r\n#Add Cargo to Path\r\nUSER node\r\n    ENV PATH=\"/root/.cargo/bin:${PATH}\"\r\nUSER root\r\n\r\n# git auto complete\r\nCOPY --chown=node:node .git-completion.bash /home/node/.git-completion.bash\r\n\r\n# node user's bash setup\r\nCOPY --chown=node:node setup-profile.sh /home/node/setup-profile.sh\r\nRUN . /home/node/setup-profile.sh\r\n\r\n# install slither\r\nRUN pip3 install slither-analyzer\r\n\r\n#Get Foundry\r\nUSER node\r\n\r\nRUN curl -L https://foundry.paradigm.xyz | bash\r\nCMD /bin/bash -c \"source /home/node/.bashrc\"\r\n# CMD /bin/bash -c \"source /home/root/.bashrc\"\r\nRUN foundryup\r\n\r\n```\r\n\r\nError from docker build:\r\n```\r\n=> CACHED [10/11] RUN curl -L https://foundry.paradigm.xyz | bash         0.0s\r\n => ERROR [11/11] RUN foundryup                                            0.5s\r\n------\r\n > [11/11] RUN foundryup:\r\n#0 0.403 /bin/sh: 1: foundryup: Permission denied\r\n------\r\nerror: failed to solve: executor failed running [/bin/sh -c foundryup]: exit code: 127\r\n[2022-07-26T12:28:30.991Z] Stop (870 ms): Run: docker buildx build --load --build-arg BUILDKIT_INLINE_CACHE=1 -f /home/adam/adamdryit/customers/thallo/projects/token-vesting-staking-contracts/.devcontainer/Dockerfile -t vsc-token-vesting-staking-contracts-5760759ce41f5cd464a14ec5d4c5f955 --build-arg VARIANT=focal /home/adam/adamdryit/customers/thallo/projects/token-vesting-staking-contracts/.devcontainer\r\n[2022-07-26T12:28:30.992Z] Error: Command failed: docker buildx build --load --build-arg BUILDKIT_INLINE_CACHE=1 -f /home/adam/adamdryit/customers/thallo/projects/token-vesting-staking-contracts/.devcontainer/Dockerfile -t vsc-token-vesting-staking-contracts-5760759ce41f5cd464a14ec5d4c5f955 --build-arg VARIANT=focal /home/adam/adamdryit/customers/thallo/projects/token-vesting-staking-contracts/.devcontainer\r\n[2022-07-26T12:28:30.993Z]     at GR (/home/adam/.vscode/extensions/ms-vscode-remote.remote-containers-0.241.3/dist/spec-node/devContainersSpecCLI.js:240:1436)\r\n[2022-07-26T12:28:30.993Z]     at processTicksAndRejections (node:internal/process/task_queues:96:5)\r\n[2022-07-26T12:28:30.993Z]     at async Hu (/home/adam/.vscode/extensions/ms-vscode-remote.remote-containers-0.241.3/dist/spec-node/devContainersSpecCLI.js:239:2796)\r\n[2022-07-26T12:28:30.993Z]     at async tb (/home/adam/.vscode/extensions/ms-vscode-remote.remote-containers-0.241.3/dist/spec-node/devContainersSpecCLI.js:239:1779)\r\n[2022-07-26T12:28:30.993Z]     at async QR (/home/adam/.vscode/extensions/ms-vscode-remote.remote-containers-0.241.3/dist/spec-node/devContainersSpecCLI.js:245:2006)\r\n[2022-07-26T12:28:30.993Z]     at async cb (/home/adam/.vscode/extensions/ms-vscode-remote.remote-containers-0.241.3/dist/s