    "body": "> @Doordashcon I was able to get foundryup to run by setting the path variable just before.\r\n> \r\n> Mine looks like this:\r\n> \r\n> ```\r\n> \r\n> SHELL [\"/bin/bash\", \"-c\"]\r\n> \r\n> RUN curl -L https://foundry.paradigm.xyz | bash\r\n> RUN source ~/.bashrc\r\n> ENV PATH=\"~/.foundry/bin:${PATH}\"\r\n> RUN foundryup\r\n> ```\r\n> \r\n> Hope it helps.\r\n\r\ncan you share your entire dockerfile?\r\nI keep getting an error:\r\n```\r\n...\r\nfoundryup: could not detect shell, manually add /home/curl_user/.foundry/bin to your PATH.\r\n------\r\nexecutor failed running [/bin/sh -c curl -L https://foundry.paradigm.xyz | sh]: exit code: 1\r\n```",
